<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<ScrollView
    xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="@color/white"
    android:scrollbars="vertical"
    tools:context=".TermsConditionActivity">
<LinearLayout
    android:orientation="vertical"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="wrap_content">
    >

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="Terms and condition"
        android:textAlignment="center"
        android:textSize="25dp"
        android:background="@color/black"
        android:textColor="@color/white"
        android:layout_margin="14dp"
        android:padding="15dp"
        android:textStyle="bold"
        android:textAllCaps="true"
        />


    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="Below are some general terms and conditions to an Online Parking Management System mobile app."
        android:textSize="20dp"
        android:textColor="@color/black"
        android:textStyle="bold"
        android:layout_margin="14dp"
        android:lineHeight="30dp"
        />

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="1. Acceptance of Terms\nBy downloading and using the Online Parking Management System mobile app, users agree to these terms and conditions. If a user does not agree with any part of these terms, they are not authorized to use the application.

\n\n2. Privacy Policy\nThe use of the app is also governed by our Privacy Policy. Read the Privacy Policy to understand our practices.

\n\n3. Registration\nTo access certain features of the Online Parking Management System mobile app, users may need to register and maintain an active account. Users must provide truthful and accurate information when registering.

\n\n4. License to Use\nUpon acceptance of these terms, the Online Parking Management System grants the user a revocable, non-exclusive license to use the App on their device in accordance with these terms.

\n\n5. Prohibited Uses\nUsers are not permitted to misuse the app. Misuse includes, but is not limited to, causing harm to the app, using the app for any illegal activities, or interfering with the regular operation of the app.

\n\n6. Booking and Payments\nUpon booking a parking spot, users agree to pay any fees associated with the parking reservation, including booking and parking fees. All payments are non-refundable unless otherwise specified in the app.

\n\n7. User Responsibilities\nUsers are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their account information and for all activities under their account.

\n\n8. Limitation of Liability\nThe Online Parking Management System will not be liable for any indirect damages including, but not limited to, loss of profits, data, or other intangible losses resulting from the use of, or inability to use, the app.

\n\n9. Changes to Terms\nThe Online Parking Management System reserves the right to modify these terms and conditions at any time. Changes will be communicated via the app or website, and continued use after notification constitutes agreement to the updated terms.

\n\n10. Termination\nThe Online Parking Management System reserves the right to suspend or terminate a user's account and access to the app, at its sole discretion, for any violations of these terms.

\n\n11. Governing Law\nThese terms shall be governed and construed in accordance with the laws of the location where the app provider is based, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.

\n\nThese terms and conditions aim to ensure the fair use of the app, protect the rights of the Online Parking Management System, and provide a clear understanding of what is expected from users. Users are advised to carefully read and understand these terms before using the app.

\n\nEnd-User License Agreement (EULA) additionally can be included to further ensure the proper use of the application software.
"
        android:textSize="20dp"
        android:textColor="@color/black"
        android:layout_margin="14dp"
        android:lineHeight="40dp"
        />

    <androidx.appcompat.widget.AppCompatButton
        android:id="@+id/backHome"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="Back to Dashboard"
        android:background="@color/black"
        android:layout_margin="14dp"
        android:layout_gravity="bottom|end"
        android:padding="20dp"
        android:textSize="16dp"
        android:textStyle="bold"
        android:textColor="@color/white"
        />

</LinearLayout>
</ScrollView>